Alkene Oxidation with H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>: Homogeneous PW<sub>12</sub> versus 5% PW<sub>12</sub>/MIL-101<xref rid="t3fn1"></xref>

Reaction condition: 0.1 M substrate, 28 mg of catalyst 5% PW12/MIL-101 or 1.4 mg of PW12 (5.8·× 10−3 mmol W), method A, 1 mL of MeCN, 50 °C, 3 h.

TOF = (moles of substrate consumed)·(moles of W)−1·time−1; determined by GC from the initial rates.

GC yield based on the substrate consumed.

Limonene 1,2-epoxide.

5 h.

Benzaldenyde was also formed.

cis-Stilbene epoxide.
